org.graalvm.polyglot

Class Value

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.graalvm.polyglot.Value

  • public final class Value
extends Object
    Represents a polyglot value. Polyglot values can either result from a host or guest language. Polyglot values are bound to a context.
    Since:
    1.0

    • Method Detail

      • getMetaObject

        public Value getMetaObject()
        Returns the meta representation of this polyglot value. The interpretation of this function depends on the guest language. For example, in JavaScript the expression context.eval("js", "42") will return the "number" string as meta object.
        Since:
        1.0

      • hasArrayElements

        public boolean hasArrayElements()
        Returns true if this polyglot value has array elements. In this case array elements can be accessed using Value.getArrayElement(long), Value.setArrayElement(long, Object) and the array size can be queried using Value.getArraySize().
        Since:
        1.0
